2 Children Killed in Floods in Iran 
Two children have been killed and several others people injured as a
result of heavy floods in west and central Iran, the Iranian news
agency IRNA said here today.
The state-run IRNA reported that of the two dead, one child was killed
in the Islamabad Village of Kahnouj in Kerman province and the other
was killed drowned in Khorramabad in Lorestan province in the past few
days. But the report did not specify the actual accidents.
The report said that several others have been injured in the cities of
Pol-e Dokhtar and Doroud in Lorestan province in the past 48 hours in
flood-related incidents.
Several rivers including Karkheh burst their banks in the province
disconnecting many rural roads.
